Manifest unseres Kaisers über den Staatenbund;
              Emperor Karl I's proclamation to the citizens of the monarchy promising to transform the Austrian half of the empire into a federal union comes too late, motivating the Hungarians to split off. The Hungarian parliament, which says its only connection to Austria is a personal union, declares Hungarian independence.
              selbstverständlich gegenstandslos, da die Autorität des Kaisers durch die „Selbstbestimmung“ ganz untergraben wurde.
